item.title: Smith - Selsted tweeter horn for 1" compression drivers
item.description:
This is a design inspired by the Smith Selsted tweeter. The original one was for a 0.5" driver, and these are not that common, so I just tried to make one for a 1" driver. I have not made any measurements yet. I assume it will be usable something like 3 kHz and up. I want to test one with the large multicell. This is in fact also a multicell horn using exponential expansion in the horizontal plane and diffraction in the vertical plane.

Print with the flange flat on the bed, the version with vanes may benefit from using supports.

item.title: SMuFF-Ifc2
item.description:
This is version 2

of my previously published SMuFF-Ifc.

Originally made to overcome the lack of serial ports on the Duet3D controller board, it turned out that even on never boards like the SKR-2, running RepRap Firmware (RRF), serial ports a precious and rare.
Hence, I revived the SMuFF-Ifc project.

This time it comes in two flavors, a simple one based on a Wemos D1 module and the more poweful ESP32 DevKit / NodeMCU.

For the ESP32 I even created a PCB, which you'll find here on PCBWay, for your convenience. The smaller Wemos D1 can be easily soldered by hand, so no PCB published for this.

All the nitty-gritty details off this project you'll find on my Github repository over here, which also contains the STEP files for the housings, in order you want do add some mods to it.

item.title: Twilight Imperium 4 Board Game Box Insert Organizer
item.description:
Naughty-Dams has made a wonderful insert for Twilight Imperium. With Naughty-Dams permission I feel I have been able to improve on this amazing design. Please check out his Thingiverse page here https://www.thingiverse.com/naughty-dams/designs

Naughty-Dams has made this for quick and easy setup, I have redesigned it to last longer, support dual color printing, and none sleeved cards.

All the files to print in one color are here. If you like to print this in dual color, please download these files and the dual color files to replace them here.
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5220514

Faction Trays
I recommend printing them with supports, but some may be fine printing without.
It also best to print all these with the bottom flat on the print bed.

You have 2 options.

  1. Print Each Named Tray
  2. Or Print 16 Fac Tray Blank X16

I did buy these dice
https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01N64MMZS/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&psc=1
https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B008CZAEO2/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&psc=1
You can store them with the flag ship, or above the cards.

CARDS Sleeved Vs Non Sleeved

If you print none sleeved card trays you can store them all in the card holder tray, leaving the PLANET CARDS holder hole in the middle insert emtey.
If you do print the sleeved card holders, you will need to store the PLANET CARDS in the hole with the map tiles.

There also options to print both Creuss and STRATEGY & DICE TRAY with name or blanked ver.

If you see a X in the name, that how many you need to print.
Example: COMMERCIAL GOODS BIN X2 Print 2

There also options to print things whole if your printers large enough or print Part A or B if you have a smaller printer.

This insert does use allot of filament and will take a long time to print everything. This is for people who love this game and plan to bring out and play for many years.

As always here is my TinkerCad Link to these files
https://www.tinkercad.com/things/4ARDNK4K4hq-twlight-imperium-insert
https://www.tinkercad.com/things/jgXTgvtEJEL-twlight-imperium-insert-duel-color
